From: Adele Agent <adele@bettercomp.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix(ritzlib): Update io.ritz String functions to use reference types

The RERITZ migration changed `&x` to `@x` for references, but io.ritz
String output functions were left using raw pointer types (`*String`).

This causes type mismatches because:
- Callers pass `@s` which creates a reference (`@String`)
- Functions expect `*String` (raw pointer)
- Internally they call `string_as_ptr(@@String)` and `string_len(@String)`

The fix updates function signatures to use the appropriate reference types:
- `print_string(s: @@String)` - mutable ref (needed by string_as_ptr)
- `eprint_string(s: @@String)` - mutable ref
- `println_string(s: @@String)` - mutable ref
- `eprintln_string(s: @@String)` - mutable ref

This maintains API compatibility since callers already pass `@s`.
---
 ritzlib/io.ritz | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/ritzlib/io.ritz b/ritzlib/io.ritz
index dad45ec..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/ritzlib/io.ritz
+++ b/ritzlib/io.ritz
@@ -164,16 +164,16 @@ pub fn newline()
 # String type output functions
 # ============================================================================

-pub fn print_string(s: *String)
+pub fn print_string(s: @@String)
     sys_write(STDOUT, string_as_ptr(s), string_len(s))

-pub fn eprint_string(s: *String)
+pub fn eprint_string(s: @@String)
     sys_write(STDERR, string_as_ptr(s), string_len(s))

-pub fn println_string(s: *String)
+pub fn println_string(s: @@String)
     print_string(s)
     print_char(10)

-pub fn eprintln_string(s: *String)
+pub fn eprintln_string(s: @@String)
     eprint_string(s)
     eprint_char(10)
